### Variables
@baseUrl=http://localhost:8080

### ============================================
### BASIC ROUTES
### ============================================

### Simple GET route
GET {{baseUrl}}/hello

### ============================================
### PATH PARAMETER SYNTAX - TWO STYLES
### ============================================

### Style 1: Colon syntax (:name)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hello/John

### Style 2: Curly braces syntax ({id})
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/123

### Multiple path parameters
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/10/post/20

### ============================================
### EXACT MATCH vs PREFIX MATCH
### ============================================

### GET: Exact match only
# ✅ Will match /api/users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### GET: Exact match with subpath (should fail)
# ❌ Will NOT match /api/users/123
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/123

### GETPrefix: Matches base path (with redirect)
# Note: Without trailing slash causes redirect
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products

### GETPrefix: Matches base path with trailing slash
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/

### GETPrefix: Matches all sub-paths
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/123

### GETPrefix: Matches deep sub-paths
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/search

### ============================================
### POST METHODS: EXACT vs PREFIX
### ============================================

### POST: Exact match
POST {{baseUrl}}/greet

### POSTPrefix: Matches sub-paths
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/submit/order

### POSTPrefix: Matches deep sub-paths
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/submit/payment/process

### ============================================
### PUT METHODS: EXACT vs PREFIX
### ============================================

### PUT: Exact match
PUT {{baseUrl}}/update/123

### PUTPrefix: Matches sub-paths
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/update/product/123

### PUTPrefix: Matches deep sub-paths
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/update/user/456/profile

### ============================================
### DELETE METHODS: EXACT vs PREFIX
### ============================================

### DELETE: Exact match
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/delete/123

### DELETEPrefix: Matches sub-paths
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/remove/item/456

### DELETEPrefix: Matches deep sub-paths
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/remove/user/789/avatar

### ============================================
### PATCH METHOD: EXACT vs PREFIX
### ============================================

### PATCH: Exact match
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/patch/123

### PATCHPrefix: Matches sub-paths
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/patch/resource/789

### ============================================
### ANY METHOD: ACCEPTS ALL HTTP METHODS
### ============================================

### ANY: Exact match - accepts any HTTP method
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/flexible

### ANY: Test with POST
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/flexible

### ANY: Test with PUT
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/flexible

### ANY: Test with DELETE
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/flexible

### ANYPrefix: Matches all methods and sub-paths
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/wildcard/

### ANYPrefix: POST on sub-path
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/wildcard/create

### ANYPrefix: PUT on deep sub-path
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/wildcard/update/123

### ANYPrefix: DELETE on sub-path
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/wildcard/remove/456

### ANYPrefix: PATCH on sub-path
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/wildcard/patch/789

### ============================================
### KEY OBSERVATIONS
### ============================================
#
# 1. Path Parameter Syntax:
#    - Colon syntax: /hello/:name
#    - Curly braces: /user/{id}
#    - Both work the same way
#
# 2. Exact Match (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH):
#    - Only matches the exact path
#    - /api/users matches /api/users
#    - /api/users does NOT match /api/users/123
#
# 3. Prefix Match (GETPrefix, POSTPrefix, etc.):
#    - Matches the path and all sub-paths
#    - /api/products matches:
#      * /api/products/ (with redirect)
#      * /api/products/123
#      * /api/products/search
#      * /api/products/category/electronics
#
# 4. Use Cases:
#    - Exact: Specific endpoints with known paths
#    - Prefix: Catch-all handlers, file servers, proxies
#
# 5. ANY Method:
#    - Accepts ALL HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, etc.)
#    - ANY: Exact path match for any method
#    - ANYPrefix: Matches any method on path and sub-paths
#    - Use cases: Generic handlers, webhooks, debugging endpoints
#
### ============================================